    <acknowledgements>
        <title/>
        <mediaobject>
            <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="images/Newton_Comet1680.jpg" format="jpeg" align="center"
                    width="6in" scalefit="1"/>
            </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
        <para>C/1680 V1, also called the Great Comet of 1680, Kirch's Comet, and Newton's Comet, has
            the distinction of being the first comet discovered by telescope. The orbit of C/1680
            V1, fit to a parabola, as shown in Isaac Newton's <emphasis>Principia</emphasis>. Isaac
            Newton used observations of C/1680 V1 to test and verify Kepler's laws of planetary
            motion. </para>
    </acknowledgements>
